{title: Stirring Up The Ashes}
{artist: Hank Thompson}
{composer: unknown}

[G]I’m stirring up the [E7]ashes of an [C]old flame of mine
[D7]Stomping any ember that may [G]still be left [D7]behind
If I [G]find the spark still glowing from the [C]love that we once knew
Then [D7]I’ll keep stirring ashes till I’ve forgotten [G]you
When [D7]flames of love are leaping they [G]seem to seek the sky
But a [A7]wisp of wilting water was your [D7]each and every lie
The [G]flame that once was raging has [C]simmered to the ground
And [D7]I’m stirring ashes to be sure you’re not [G]around
I’m stirring up the [E7]ashes from an [C]old love affair
To be [D7]certain nothing lingers to be [G]sure that I don’t [D7]care
A [G]coal left unattended may be [C]tempted by the wind
To [D7]flame up in a romance that I never want [G]again
I [D7]was just a sacrifice [G]to your lover’s power
A [A7]lamb led to the slaughter as my [D7]hopes reach high and higher
